---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'
import BoneTexture from '../assets/images/frame-bio_bone-texture.svg'
import CollagenTexture from '../assets/images/frame-bio_collagen-texture.svg'
import FrameBioFigureTwo from '../assets/images/frame-bio_figure-2.svg'
import FrameBioFigure from '../assets/images/frame-bio_figure-leaning-stretch.svg'
import PillsTexture from '../assets/images/frame-bio_pills-texture.svg'
import FrameBioPipelineGrid from '../assets/images/frame-bio_pipeline-grid-section.svg'
import SkinBoneAxisLockup from '../assets/images/frame-bio_skin-bone-axis-lockup.svg'
import highResImage from '../assets/images/high-res-exosome-image.png'
import Header from '../components/ui/Header.astro'
import ProductCard from '../components/ui/ProductCard.astro'
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout>
  <Header />
  <main class="pb-0">
    <section id="about" class="md:pt-0">
      <h2 class="sr-only">About Frame Bio</h2>
      <div class="wrapper">
        <div
          id="targeted-therapies-grid"
          class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-(--site-padding-base) gap-y-(--site-padding-lg)"
        >
          <FrameBioFigure
            class="hidden md:block h-auto max-w-lg mr-auto lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat"
          />
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-(--site-padding-base) w-full lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat">
            <h3>Targeted therapies for the</h3>
            <SkinBoneAxisLockup class="max-w-md" />
            <h4 class="text-secondary">
              A Novel Paradigm for Relieving Structural Diseases & Disorders
            </h4>
            <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-sm)">
              <p>
                With nearly one-third of the world's people affected by skin diseases, and more than
                200 million people worldwide suffering from osteoporosis, there is a great need for
                therapies targeting skin and bone issues. At Frame Bio, we're developing better
                methods for delivering such therapies directly to bones, joints, tendons, and
                collagen with the goal of enhancing the body's natural repair processes.
              </p>
              <p>
                Emerging research suggests that our skin and bones may be more connected than we
                thought. Through hormones, vitamins, and the immune system, it appears that these
                two systems talk to each other; when one is struggling, the other often does too.
                This crosstalk, known as the skin-bone axis, is seen in the relationship between
                skin diseases and bone disease and serves as inspiration for Frame Bio's research.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Treatment Tags - Second Row, Spanning Both Columns -->
          <div
            class="md:col-span-2 grid grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4 gap-4 lsa lsa-slide-up no-repeat"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 flex-shrink-0 bg-secondary rounded-full animate-pulse"></div>
              <p class="h5 font-museo-slab-rounded">Bone</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 flex-shrink-0 bg-secondary rounded-full animate-pulse"></div>
              <p class="h5 font-museo-slab-rounded">Collagen</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 flex-shrink-0 bg-secondary rounded-full animate-pulse"></div>
              <p class="h5 font-museo-slab-rounded">Tendons/Joints</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 flex-shrink-0 bg-secondary rounded-full animate-pulse"></div>
              <p class="h5 font-museo-slab-rounded">Cartilage</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <FrameBioFigure
            class="block md:hidden h-auto max-w-lg mr-auto lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="our-tech">
      <div class="wrapper">
        <div
          class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_500px] gap-(--site-padding-xl) justify-items-center items-center"
        >
          <!-- Left Column: Text Content -->
          <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-base) lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat">
            <h2 class="text-secondary font-museo-slab-rounded uppercase">CORE TECHNOLOGY</h2>
            <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-sm)">
              <p>
                One of the best ways to improve the success of a drug in development is to ensure
                that it reaches the areas of the body that need it most. This cannot only improve
                the overall efficacy of the drug, but also reduce the negative side effects that can
                often accompany off-target delivery. When therapeutics are directed to where they're
                needed most versus being diluted across unrelated organs and bodily systems, their
                potency is naturally increased.
              </p>
              <p>
                At Frame Bio, we've employed a novel method of extracellular vesicle (EV) drug
                encapsulation developed by Mercury Bio Inc. to deliver therapies directly to injured
                bone, joints, and other tissues. Mercury Bio's yEV™ technology works with the
                body's natural transport system—targeting cells with a high level of precision and
                depositing molecular therapies directly to them.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Right Column: Exosome Image with Static Annotations -->
          <div
            class="relative w-full h-auto max-w-[500px] max-h-[500px] mx-auto text-accent lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat"
          >
            <Image
              src={highResImage}
              alt="High resolution exosome structure"
              class="drop-shadow-2xl relative"
              width={highResImage.width}
              height={highResImage.height}
            />

            <!-- First annotation - center left area -->
            <div class="absolute top-full left-0 w-[180px]">
              <p class="text-xs leading-tight">
                An extracellular vesicle is a nanoscale, membrane-bound particle (about 30-1000
                nanometers in diameter) that cells naturally release for intercellular
                communication. They carry proteins, lipids, and nucleic acids to transmit signals
                and regulate the behavior of other cells.
              </p>
              <!-- Horizontal line with circle - rotate with CSS transform as needed -->
              <svg
                class="absolute -top-20 left-1/2 -rotate-60 w-[150px] h-[20px]"
                viewBox="0 0 150 20"
              >
                <line x1="0" y1="10" x2="140" y2="10" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2"
                ></line>
                <circle cx="140" cy="10" r="3" fill="var(--color-accent)"></circle>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="products" class="overflow-x-hidden">
      <div class="wrapper">
        <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-base)">
          <h2 class="text-secondary font-museo-slab-rounded uppercase lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat">
            Product Development
          </h2>
          <p
            class="mb-(--site-padding-lg) lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat max-w-(--content-max-width)"
          >
            Currently, Frame Bio is researching three unique product lines, each addressing
            different components of the skin-bone axis, with the aim of improving quality of life
            for millions of people suffering from inflammation and discomfort tied to bone disease
            and connective tissue disorders.
          </p>

          <!-- Product Cards -->
          <div class="h-full flex flex-col gap-(--site-padding-lg)">
            <ProductCard
              title="Collagen Regeneration"
              description={[
                'Collagen is a fiber-like structural protein found in tendons, ligaments, joints, and bones. Many collagen diseases are autoimmune, resulting from an overactive immune system that mistakenly attacks healthy collagen. Current treatments for collagen disorders tend to focus on reducing inflammation and improving mobility. This can be accomplished with medication, surgery, dietary supplements, or a combination of these.',
                "Frame Bio's research aims to develop targeted collagen therapies that augment natural regenerative processes. This means fewer surgical interventions and a decreased need for medications that affect the entire body. By delivering signaling proteins to the source of skin and bone disease, Frame Bio's novel therapeutics look beyond mere symptom relief in favor of returning tissues to fundamentally healthier states.",
              ]}
              image={CollagenTexture}
              imageAlt="Illustration of collagen regeneration"
              numeral={1}
            />

            <ProductCard
              title="Bone Regeneration via BMP-2"
              description={[
                'Bones are in a constant state of growth and deterioration. When the balance between these processes is altered, bone density is affected. Historically, treatment of low bone density has included dietary supplements and medications called bisphosphonates. Unwanted side effects, and the low benefit of long-term use, have revealed the need for better treatment options. Recent research has explored the use of a naturally produced protein called BMP, or bone morphogenetic protein. BMP-2 is currently approved by the FDA to heal fractures in certain bones, and in spinal fusion surgery. While the success of various forms of BMP in improving bone remodeling has been demonstrated, better delivery methods are needed to control the timing and location of BMP release within the body.',
                "Frame Bio's solution has been to turn to hydroxyapatite, a form of calcium that is found naturally in bones and teeth, which can improve the binding of BMP-2 to bone tissues, thereby delivering it directly to damaged bone. Through a research partnership with Himed LLC, one of the world's leading producers of hydroxyapatite technologies used to enhance orthopedic devices, we've identified a means of deploying BMP-2 in bone scaffolding materials commonly used to repair hard tissue breaks and fractures. And we're future-proofing this application method by exploring how it translates into the new world of patient-specific 3D-printed implants, so that as healthcare becomes even more personalized and customized, our technology is ready.",
              ]}
              image={BoneTexture}
              imageAlt="Illustration of bone regeneration"
              numeral={2}
            />

            <ProductCard
              title="Nutraceutical Development"
              description={[
                'A nutraceutical is a food-derived product—ranging from isolated nutrients to herbal extracts—used for health benefits beyond basic nutrition. In the context of bone and joint health, widely studied examples include calcium and vitamin D for maintaining bone density; collagen peptides, glucosamine, and chondroitin for supporting cartilage and joint comfort; omega-3 fatty acids and curcumin for their anti-inflammatory properties; and isoflavones or hyaluronic acid for reinforcing bone strength and joint lubrication.',
                "Even when these compounds have plausible biological roles, their benefits are often limited by poor bioavailability and off-target delivery, leaving only small amounts to reach bone or cartilage in effective concentrations. The use of a targeted drug delivery system addresses these challenges, opening the door to maximizing nutraceutical efficacy. Frame Bio's initial focus is on natural compounds with strong anti-inflammatory activity that may help reduce reliance on NSAID painkillers for connective tissue pain.",
              ]}
              image={PillsTexture}
              imageAlt="Illustration of pill regeneration"
              numeral={3}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="pipeline" class="bg-primary text-primary-content overflow-x-hidden">
      <div class="wrapper xl:pt-100">
        <!-- Header with Title and Figure -->
        <div
          class="relative grid xl:grid-cols-2 items-end gap-(--site-padding-base) mb-(--site-padding-2xl)"
        >
          <div class="xl:order-2 lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat xl:absolute xl:-right-100 w-full">
            <Image
              src={FrameBioFigureTwo}
              alt="Illustration of person in a crow pose yoga position"
              class="h-auto mx-auto block w-full max-w-xl"
            />
          </div>
          <h2
            class="text-secondary text-center xl:text-nowrap font-museo-slab-rounded uppercase text-4xl lg:text-5xl lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat"
          >
            Drug Development Pipeline
          </h2>
        </div>

        <!-- Pipeline Charts -->

        <!-- Desktop -->
        <div class="hidden xl:block space-y-(--site-padding-lg) lsa lsa-slide-up no-repeat">
          <!-- Column Headers -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-(--site-padding-base) mb-(--site-padding-base)">
            <div></div>
            <!-- Empty space for row labels -->
            <div class="text-center">
              <h4 class="text-accent uppercase text-xl">Discovery</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <h4 class="text-accent uppercase text-xl">Pre-Clinical</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <h4 class="text-accent uppercase text-xl">IND-Enabling</h4>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-(--site-padding-base) items-center mb-(--site-padding-lg)"
          >
            <!-- Row Labels -->
            <div class="space-y-8">
              <div class="space-y-2">
                <h4 class="text-xl font-museo-slab-rounded font-bold uppercase text-secondary">
                  BMP-2
                </h4>
                <p class="leading-tight">
                  <span class="uppercase"
                    >Bone Morphogenic<br />
                    Protein</span
                  >
                </p>
              </div>
              <!-- Row Label -->
              <div class="space-y-2">
                <h4 class="font-museo-slab-rounded font-bold uppercase text-secondary text-xl">
                  Collagen 1
                </h4>
                <p class="leading-tight">
                  <span class="uppercase"
                    >Collagen Protein<br />
                    Regeneration</span
                  >
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Grid Background (3 sections) -->
            <div class="col-span-3 relative">
              <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
                <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
                <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
              </div>

              <!-- 1st Progress Bar Overlay -->
              <div class="absolute top-12 left-0 w-1/2 flex items-center">
                <div class="relative w-full h-6 flex items-center">
                  <!-- Circle -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full z-1"
                  >
                  </div>
                  <!-- Line -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute left-2.5 h-1 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full"
                    style="width: 100%;"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- 2nd Progress Bar Overlay -->
              <div class="absolute bottom-12 left-0 w-1/4 flex items-center">
                <div class="relative w-full h-6 flex items-center">
                  <!-- Circle -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full z-1"
                  >
                  </div>
                  <!-- Line -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute left-2.5 h-1 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full"
                    style="width: 100%;"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Footer Text -->
          <div class="flex justify-between gap-8">
            <p class="max-w-2xl">
              Frame Bio has two therapies already under development: one which targets bone
              regeneration, and another that aims to strengthen connective tissues by catalyzing
              collagen production. Both product lines harness the intercellular communications that
              occur with extra cellular vesicles to deliver therapeutics which trigger the body's
              natural healing processes.
            </p>

            <!-- Caption -->

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-accent">
              <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                height="24px"
                width="24px"
                viewBox="0 -960 960 960"
                fill="currentColor"
                class="size-8"
                ><path
                  d="M401 0q-83 0-156-31.5t-127.5-86Q63-172 31.5-245T0-400q0-83 31.5-156t86-127.5Q172-738 245-769.5T401-801q10 0 19.5.5T440-799v80q-10-1-19.5-1.5T401-721q-134 0-227.5 93.5T80-400q0 133 93.5 226.5T401-80q133 0 226.5-93.5T721-400h80q0 82-31.5 155t-86 127.5q-54.5 54.5-127 86T401 0Zm131-212L360-384v-216h80v184l148 148-56 56Zm342-268q-23-142-120-246.5T520-866v-82q171 37 290.5 165T955-480h-81Zm-163 0q-19-75-69.5-132T520-698v-85q103 32 177 113.5T793-480h-82Z"
                ></path></svg
              >
              <p class="text-sm text-accent leading-tight">
                Want to stay connected to Frame Bio's product development process? <a
                  href="#"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener"
                  class="link text-sm leading-tight">Follow our company on LinkedIn</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Mobile -->
        <div
          class="mx-auto flex flex-col items-center xl:hidden gap-(--site-padding-lg) lsa lsa-slide-up no-repeat"
        >
          <!-- Column Headers -->
          <div
            class="w-full grid grid-cols-[1fr_4fr_4fr] gap-(--site-padding-base) mb-(--site-padding-base)"
          >
            <!-- Empty space for row labels -->
            <div></div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-secondary uppercase">BMP-2</h4>
              <p class="leading-tight">
                <span class="uppercase"
                  >Bone Morphogenic<br />
                  Protein</span
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-secondary uppercase">Collagen 1</h4>
              <p class="leading-tight">
                <span class="uppercase"
                  >Collagen Protein<br />
                  Regeneration</span
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Discovery Row -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[1fr_4fr_4fr] justify-items-center items-center">
            <h4 class="[writing-mode:vertical-rl] mr-(--site-padding-base) text-accent uppercase">
              Discovery
            </h4>
            <div class="relative">
              <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
              <!-- BMP-2 Progress Bar for Discovery -->
              <div class="absolute inset-0 flex justify-center items-center">
                <div class="relative h-full w-6 flex justify-center">
                  <!-- Circle -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute top-0 w-5 h-5 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full z-1"
                  >
                  </div>
                  <!-- Line -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute top-2.5 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-1 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full"
                    style="height: 200%"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="relative">
              <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
              <!-- Collagen Progress Bar for Discovery -->
              <div class="absolute inset-0 flex justify-center items-center">
                <div class="relative h-full w-6 flex justify-center">
                  <!-- Circle -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute top-0 w-5 h-5 bg-white rounded-full z-1 shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)]"
                  >
                  </div>
                  <!-- Line -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute top-2.5 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-1 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full"
                    style="height: 100%"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Pre-Clinical Row -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[1fr_4fr_4fr] justify-items-center items-center">
            <h4 class="[writing-mode:vertical-rl] mr-(--site-padding-base) text-accent uppercase">
              Pre-Clinical
            </h4>
            <div class="relative">
              <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
            </div>
            <div class="relative">
              <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- IND-Enabling Row -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[1fr_4fr_4fr] justify-items-center items-center">
            <h4 class="[writing-mode:vertical-rl] mr-(--site-padding-base) text-accent uppercase">
              IND-Enabling
            </h4>
            <div class="relative">
              <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
            </div>
            <div class="relative">
              <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Mobile Footer Text -->
          <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-base) mt-(--site-padding-lg)">
            <p class="text-sm">
              Frame Bio has two therapies already under development: one which targets bone
              regeneration, and another that aims to strengthen connective tissues by catalyzing
              collagen production. Both product lines harness the intercellular communications that
              occur with extra cellular vesicles to deliver therapeutics which trigger the body's
              natural healing processes.
            </p>

            <!-- Bottom Icon/Text for Mobile -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-accent">
              <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                height="24px"
                width="24px"
                viewBox="0 -960 960 960"
                fill="currentColor"
                class="size-6 flex-shrink-0"
                ><path
                  d="M401 0q-83 0-156-31.5t-127.5-86Q63-172 31.5-245T0-400q0-83 31.5-156t86-127.5Q172-738 245-769.5T401-801q10 0 19.5.5T440-799v80q-10-1-19.5-1.5T401-721q-134 0-227.5 93.5T80-400q0 133 93.5 226.5T401-80q133 0 226.5-93.5T721-400h80q0 82-31.5 155t-86 127.5q-54.5 54.5-127 86T401 0Zm131-212L360-384v-216h80v184l148 148-56 56Zm342-268q-23-142-120-246.5T520-866v-82q171 37 290.5 165T955-480h-81Zm-163 0q-19-75-69.5-132T520-698v-85q103 32 177 113.5T793-480h-82Z"
                ></path></svg
              >
              <p class="text-xs leading-tight">
                Want to stay connected to Frame Bio's product development process? <a
                  href="#"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener"
                  class="link text-xs leading-tight">Follow our company on LinkedIn</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="relative">
      <!-- Pulse Effect -->
      <div
        class="left-0 top-0 absolute w-full h-full md:w-[calc(100%-var(--site-padding-4xl))] xl:w-[calc(100%-var(--site-padding-5xl))] shadow-[0_0_20px] shadow-secondary z-0 animate-pulse"
      >
      </div>
      <!-- Background -->
      <div
        id="contact-bg"
        class="left-0 top-0 absolute w-full h-full md:w-[calc(100%-var(--site-padding-4xl))] xl:w-[calc(100%-var(--site-padding-5xl))] bg-primary z-2"
      >
      </div>
      <div class="wrapper relative z-2">
        <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-base) md:pr-(--site-padding-md)">
          <h2 class="text-secondary font-museo-slab-rounded uppercase lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat">
            Contact Frame Bio
          </h2>
          <p class="lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat">
            <strong>Want to help advance a new paradigm for bone and joint health?</strong> We're building
            next-generation therapies that go beyond managing symptoms—aiming to repair, restore, and
            truly change the trajectory of skeletal and connective tissue disorders. If you're developing
            novel therapeutics for skin and bone disorders, or investing in breakthrough ideas, we want
            to connect with you.
          </p>

          <form
            id="contact-form"
            class="space-y-(--site-padding-sm) lsa no-repeat"
            method="POST"
            action="/api/forms/contact"
            data-netlify="true"
            data-netlify-honeypot="bot-field"
          >
            <!-- Honeypot field - hidden from users, catches bots -->
            <div style="display: none;">
              <label>Don't fill this out if you're human: <input name="bot-field" /></label>
            </div>

            <!-- First and Last Name -->
            <fieldset class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-(--site-padding-sm)">
              <legend class="sr-only">Personal Information</legend>
              <label class="sr-only" for="firstName">First Name (required)</label>
              <input
                type="text"
                name="firstName"
                id="firstName"
                placeholder="First Name*"
                required
                aria-required="true"
              />
              <label class="sr-only" for="lastName">Last Name (required)</label>
              <input
                type="text"
                name="lastName"
                id="lastName"
                placeholder="Last Name*"
                required
                aria-required="true"
              />
            </fieldset>

            <!-- Business Name -->
            <fieldset>
              <legend class="sr-only">Business Name</legend>
              <label class="sr-only" for="businessName">Business Name (required)</label>
              <input
                type="text"
                name="businessName"
                id="businessName"
                placeholder="Business Name*"
                required
                aria-required="true"
              />
            </fieldset>

            <fieldset>
              <legend class="sr-only">Job Title</legend>
              <label class="sr-only" for="jobTitle">Job Title (required)</label>
              <input
                type="text"
                name="jobTitle"
                id="jobTitle"
                placeholder="Job Title*"
                required
                aria-required="true"
              />
            </fieldset>

            <!-- Email + Phone -->
            <fieldset class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-(--site-padding-sm)">
              <legend class="sr-only">Contact Information</legend>
              <label class="sr-only" for="email">Email Address (required)</label>
              <input
                type="email"
                name="email"
                id="email"
                placeholder="Email*"
                required
                aria-required="true"
                aria-describedby="email-help"
              />
              <label class="sr-only" for="phone">Phone Number (required)</label>
              <input
                type="tel"
                name="phone"
                id="phone"
                placeholder="Phone*"
                required
                aria-required="true"
              />
            </fieldset>

            <!-- Message textarea -->
            <fieldset>
              <legend class="sr-only">Message (optional)</legend>
              <textarea
                name="message"
